---
import VizLayout from '../../layouts/VizLayout.astro';
const title = "2.2 Sorting Bank · GATE DA";
---
<VizLayout {title} currentPath="/module2/2-2-bank" pageCss="/assets/css/pages/1-1-questions.css">

<div class="gd-breadcrumb">
  <a href="/index.html">Home</a><span>›</span>
  <a href="/module2.html">Module 2</a><span>›</span>
  2.2 Bank
</div>
<a class="gd-pill-link" href="/module2/2-2-questions.html">← Practice Questions (10 Qs)</a>

<div class="gd-viz-header">
  <div style="display:flex;gap:8px;margin-bottom:10px;flex-wrap:wrap;">
    <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--subject">Module 2 · DSA</span>
    <span class="gd-badge gd-badge--pyq">20 questions · MCQ / NAT / MSQ</span>
  </div>
  <h1 id="top">2.2 Sorting — Question Bank</h1>
  <p>Extended practice: counting/radix/bucket sort, external merge, quickselect, in-place merge, timsort, three-way partition, stability, partial sort and string sorting.</p>
</div>

<div class="q-score-bar">
  <div>
    <div class="q-score-bar__count"><span id="score-num">0</span> / 20</div>
    <div class="q-score-bar__label">correct answers revealed</div>
  </div>
  <button class="q-score-bar__reset" onclick="resetAll()">Reset all</button>
</div>

<div class="q-list">

  <div class="q-card" id="qc1">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q1</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Counting sort on $n$ keys in range $[0,k]$ runs in</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q1-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(n \log n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(n+k)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(nk)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="1" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(n^2)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(1,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q1-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) $O(n+k)$.</span></b> Linear when $k = O(n)$; it is not comparison-based, so it beats the $n\log n$ bound.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc2">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q2</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Radix sort with $d$ digits using a stable counting sort per digit runs in</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q2-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(d(n+b))$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(n \log n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(n^2)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="2" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(d \log n)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(2,'mcq','A')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q2-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (A) $O(d(n+b))$.</span></b> $b$ = base; each of the $d$ passes is a stable $O(n+b)$ counting sort.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc3">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q3</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">External merge sort is used when</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q3-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> data fits in cache</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> data is too large to fit in main memory</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> keys are integers</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="3" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> the array is already sorted</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(3,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q3-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> It sorts runs that fit in RAM then merges them from disk — minimizing I/O.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc4">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q4</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Quickselect finds the k-th smallest element in expected</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q4-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="4" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="4" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(n \log n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="4" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(n^2)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="4" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(\log n)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(4,'mcq','A')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q4-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (A) $O(n)$ expected.</span></b> Partition once and recurse into only one side; expected linear, worst case $O(n^2)$.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc5">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q5</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">In-place merge sort reduces space to $O(1)$ but typically increases</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q5-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> stability</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> time complexity or implementation complexity</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> cache misses to zero</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="5" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> the number of comparisons to $O(n)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(5,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q5-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> In-place merging is intricate and often raises the constant factors or time.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc6">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q6</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Timsort (Python/Java) is a hybrid of</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q6-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> quick + heap sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> merge + insertion sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> radix + counting sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="6" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> bubble + selection sort</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(6,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q6-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> It runs insertion sort on small runs then merges them — stable and adaptive.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc7">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q7</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Three-way partitioning (Dutch national flag) is most useful when the array has</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q7-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="7" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> all distinct keys</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="7" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> many duplicate keys</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="7" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> negative numbers</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="7" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> floating-point keys</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(7,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q7-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) many duplicates.</span></b> It groups equal keys in one pass, avoiding quick sort's degradation on duplicates.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc8">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q8</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Stability matters most when</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q8-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> sorting integers</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> sorting records by a secondary key after a primary sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> the array is small</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="8" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> using $O(1)$ space</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(8,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q8-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> A stable sort preserves the earlier ordering of equal keys — essential for multi-key sorts.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc9">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q9</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Partial sort to get the top 3 of $n=8$ elements using a min-heap of size 3 needs at most how many heap operations of $O(\log 3)$? Give the count of elements processed.</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q9-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">elements</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(9,7.9,8.1)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q9-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 8.</span></b> Each of the 8 elements is processed once against the size-3 heap.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc10">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q10</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Sorting an array of strings of total length $L$ by comparison costs</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q10-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="10" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(n \log n)$ ignoring string length</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="10" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(L \log n)$ accounting for comparisons</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="10" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(L)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="10" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(n^2)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(10,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q10-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> Each comparison can scan up to the string length, so total work is $O(L \log n)$.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc11">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q11</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Heap sort first builds a heap in $O(n)$ then extracts $n$ times, giving total</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q11-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="11" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> $O(n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="11" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> $O(n \log n)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="11" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> $O(n^2)$</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="11" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> $O(\log n)$</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(11,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q11-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) $O(n \log n)$.</span></b> Build is $O(n)$ but $n$ extract-max operations cost $O(n \log n)$ overall.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc12">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q12</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Number of comparisons selection sort makes on $n=5$ elements is $n(n-1)/2$. Compute it.</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q12-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">comparisons</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(12,9.9,10.1)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q12-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 10.</span></b> $5 \cdot 4 / 2 = 10$ comparisons regardless of input order.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc13">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q13</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Which sort is NOT comparison-based?</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q13-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="13" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> Merge sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="13" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> Counting sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="13" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> Quick sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="13" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> Heap sort</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(13,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q13-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) Counting sort.</span></b> It uses key values as indices, bypassing the $\Omega(n \log n)$ comparison bound.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc14">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q14</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Bucket sort gives expected $O(n)$ when input is</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q14-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="14" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> uniformly distributed over a known range</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="14" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> reverse sorted</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="14" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> all equal</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="14" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> arbitrary</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(14,'mcq','A')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q14-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (A).</span></b> Uniform distribution spreads keys evenly across buckets, each sorted in $O(1)$ expected.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc15">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q15</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Merge sort makes how many levels of recursion for $n=16$? (depth of the recursion tree)</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q15-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">levels</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(15,3.9,4.1)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q15-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 4.</span></b> $\log_2 16 = 4$ levels of halving.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc16">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q16</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Which sort is adaptive (faster on nearly-sorted input)?</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q16-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="16" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> Merge sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="16" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> Insertion sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="16" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> Heap sort</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="16" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> Selection sort</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(16,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q16-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B) Insertion sort.</span></b> On a nearly-sorted array it approaches $O(n)$.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc17">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q17</span><span class="q-type q-type--msq">MSQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks · no negative</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Which sorts are NOT stable? (Select all.)</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q17-opts">
      <label class="q-opt q-opt--msq"><input type="checkbox" data-q="17" data-val="A"> <span class="q-opt-key">A</span> Quick sort</label>
      <label class="q-opt q-opt--msq"><input type="checkbox" data-q="17" data-val="B"> <span class="q-opt-key">B</span> Heap sort</label>
      <label class="q-opt q-opt--msq"><input type="checkbox" data-q="17" data-val="C"> <span class="q-opt-key">C</span> Merge sort</label>
      <label class="q-opt q-opt--msq"><input type="checkbox" data-q="17" data-val="D"> <span class="q-opt-key">D</span> Selection sort (standard)</label>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkMsq(17,['A','B','D'])">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q17-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (A), (B), (D).</span></b> Merge sort is stable. Quick, heap and standard selection sort are not.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc18">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q18</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Shell sort improves insertion sort by</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q18-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="18" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> using a heap</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="18" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> comparing elements separated by a gap that shrinks</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="18" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> partitioning around a pivot</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="18" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> counting occurrences</div>
    </div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="check(18,'mcq','B')">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q18-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ (B).</span></b> Gap sequences move elements long distances early, reducing later work.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc19">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q19</span><span class="q-type q-type--nat">NAT</span><span class="q-diff">★</span><span class="q-marks">1 mark</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">Bubble sort on a sorted array of $n=6$ (with early-exit) makes how many passes before stopping?</div>
    <div class="q-nat"><input class="q-nat__input" id="q19-input" type="number" step="any" placeholder="your answer"><span class="q-nat__label">passes</span></div>
    <div class="q-footer">
      <button class="q-check-btn" onclick="checkNat(19,0.9,1.1)">Check</button>
      <div class="q-answer" id="q19-ans"><b><span class="ans-correct">✓ 1.</span></b> One clean pass with no swaps triggers early termination.</div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="q-card" id="qc20">
    <div class="q-header"><span class="q-num">Q20</span><span class="q-type">MCQ</span><span class="q-diff">★★</span><span class="q-marks">2 marks</span></div>
    <div class="q-body">The minimum number of comparisons to sort 3 elements in the worst case is</div>
    <div class="q-options" id="q20-opts">
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="20" data-val="A" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">A</span> 2</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="20" data-val="B" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">B</span> 3</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="20" data-val="C" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">C</span> 4</div>
      <div class="q-opt" data-q="20" data-val="D" onclick="selectOpt(this)"><span class="q-opt-key">D</span> 6</div>
    </div>
